# s239_appearance_arc_visual_demo — the canvas-observable arc's
# payoff, exaggerated for visual confidence.
#
# Not a regression smoke. No asserts, no teardown — leaves the
# document populated so Scott can SEE the result. The trace channel
# already passed (smokes 36 / 37 / 38 = 11+13+13 asserts clean);
# this script is purely the visual half of three-channel acceptance.
#
# Three rects, three colours, three thicknesses. Each rect uses all
# four arc verbs in sequence (geometry, fill, stroke colour, stroke
# width) so the final state of the canvas shows every appearance
# axis the script surface now controls.
#
# Layout (page-space, user coordinates, Y-up):
#
#   left rect   (orange fill, navy outline,  20px wide)  at x=  0
#   middle rect (lime fill,   magenta outline, 40px wide) at x=200
#   right rect  (yellow fill, black outline, 80px wide)  at x=400
#
# Each rect is 150×200. Widths 20 / 40 / 80 are stepped 2× so the
# proportional difference is obvious. 80px is "you can't miss this"
# — half the rect's narrow dimension is outline.

#[sub] === BUILD UP ===
#[sub] Activate a fresh layer so the demo objects are isolated and
#[sub] easy to delete via the layer panel after viewing.

layers new
set demo_layer to result
layers.demo_layer rename "s239_appearance_arc_demo"
layers.demo_layer activate

#[sub] === Left rect — orange fill, navy outline, 20px wide ===
#[sub] 20px on a 150-wide rect is ~13% of the width — clearly
#[sub] visible but not overwhelming.

objects new "path"
set left to result
objects.left set_path_data "M 0 50 L 150 50 L 150 250 L 0 250 Z"
objects.left set_fill "orange"
objects.left set_stroke "navy"
objects.left set_stroke_width 20.0

#[sub] === Middle rect — lime fill, magenta outline, 40px wide ===
#[sub] 40px is ~27% of the width — the outline starts to dominate.

objects new "path"
set middle to result
objects.middle set_path_data "M 200 50 L 350 50 L 350 250 L 200 250 Z"
objects.middle set_fill "lime"
objects.middle set_stroke "magenta"
objects.middle set_stroke_width 40.0

#[sub] === Right rect — yellow fill, black outline, 80px wide ===
#[sub] 80px is ~53% of the width — the outline is the rect's
#[sub] primary visible feature. If this doesn't render thick and
#[sub] black, something is broken.

objects new "path"
set right to result
objects.right set_path_data "M 400 50 L 550 50 L 550 250 L 400 250 Z"
objects.right set_fill "yellow"
objects.right set_stroke "black"
objects.right set_stroke_width 80.0

#[sub] === Done ===
#[sub] Three rects, three fill colours, three stroke colours, three
#[sub] step-doubled stroke widths. The s239 appearance arc closed
#[sub] in two milestones (m1 set_stroke + m2 set_stroke_width)
#[sub] and this is what it looks like.
#[sub]
#[sub] To clean up: delete the `s239_appearance_arc_demo` layer
#[sub] from the layer panel.

list
